## /etc/pve/firewall/cluster.fw — managed by bare-metal-bootstrap's
## playbooks/06-pve-firewall.yml. Do not edit by hand; changes are
## overwritten on the next run.
##
## Datacenter-wide firewall master switch + default policy. pve-firewall is
## a complete no-op cluster-wide unless enable: 1 is set HERE (not in any
## host.fw) — see PVE::Firewall::compile(). policy_in: DROP is what actually
## makes every host.fw's [RULES] meaningful; without it those rules exist
## but enforce nothing.
##
## Deliberately carries no [RULES] of its own — every node's own host.fw
## already covers the identical tailscale0/LAN-SSH/8006 policy, and this
## file is written once, cluster-wide, only after every node's host.fw is
## already staged (see the playbook's task ordering).

[OPTIONS]
enable: 1
policy_in: DROP
policy_out: ACCEPT
